      <biogHist id="md5-b9603d496a460d2a7d7e1d05448e1760">
        <p>Teacher, Farmer, Merchant, 1904-  .  Muriel Oslie was a school teacher before settling down as a  farmer in Weyburn, Saskatchewan in 1931.  In 1937 she moved to the Peace River District of  Alberta, where she operated a trading post in Martin River until the early forties and a store in  Three Creeks until 1969.  Mrs. Oslie recorded interviews with Peace River residents, and together  with her detailed diaries, she has preserved a personal history of frontier life in northern Alberta.</p>
      </biogHist>
